-- China's Shandong Province Faces Oversupply of Oil Products, dzwww.com Says
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-07-19T04:03:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-19/china-s-shandong-province-faces-oversupply-of-oil-products-dzwww-com-says.html

          
          
             China’s eastern province of Shandong
faces an oversupply of oil products, news portal  dzwww.com 
reported, citing the local petroleum and chemical association.  
 The province received 12.2 million metric tons of oil-
product supply in the first half, including 7 million tons from
domestic privately held processing plants, 3.7 million tons from
 China Petroleum & Chemical Corp.  and 1.5 million tons from
 PetroChina Co.  Fuel consumption reached 7.3 million tons during
the period, according to the report.  
 Shandong’s fuel demand will rise to 14.5 million tons this
year, up by 500,000 tons from a year earlier, it said.
Oversupply of oil products in the province will persist in the
long term, it said.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
